FBIS3-1907 "drchi042_e_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 Southeast Asia & Pacific Comparison to Qiao Shi Meets Singapore's Goh, Lee OW2702114294 OW2702114294 Article Type:BFN Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese at 0841 GMT on 27 February carries a report on Qiao Shi meeting with Singapore's Goh Chok Tong and Lee Kuan Yew. The Chinese version has been compared to the XINHUA English version entitled "Qiao Shi Meets Singapore's Goh, Lee" published in the 28 February China DAILY REPORT, page 19, revealing the following variations: Page 19, column one, paragraph ten, only sentence reads: ...mutual investments expanding. [new graf] Qiao Shi happily recalled his visit to Singapore last July and he said that he was particularly pleased to meet with Premier Goh Chok Tong and Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew again in Beijing. He added, "During my visit to your country last year, I was shown warm hospitality by your government, parliament, and people. My visit was very short, but I learned a lot." [new graf] The delegation was... (adding new paragraph and rephrasing)
